with disability services cuts — used in 2026-04-27 ep1 and ep1.rewrite\n  - The ACA marketplace quiet-downgrade story (\"thousands of Marylanders have been quietly downgrading their health insurance plans\") — introduced in 2026-04-28 ep1 and revisited in 2026-04-29 ep3\n  - Maryland's 90-day part-time legislature explanation (\"they meet in Annapolis for ninety days, the rest of the time they're lawyers, teachers, small business owners\") — used in 2026-04-26 ep3 and ep3.rewrite\n  - The wave of 25 Maryland lawmakers retiring or running for other offices framing — used in 2026-04-26 ep1, ep1.rewrite, and ep4\n  - The Beltsville Agricultural Research Center closure story as a District 19 candidate-record hook — used in 2026-04-27 ep4 and ep4.rewrite\n  - Listener's own frustration about promised candidate deep-dives not delivering — the show has now narrated this complaint back to the listener across at least five episodes; do not repeat it as a framing device again\n\nLISTENER POSITIONING:\n  • The listener is a first-time voter in the configured locale.\n  • Locale: Rockville, Montgomery County, Maryland.\n  • Their districts:\n  - U.S. Congressional District: MD-8\n  - MD Legislative District: 19\n  - MD State Senate District: 19\n  - MD House of Delegates District: 19\n  - Senatorial District: 19\n  - County Councilmanic District: 7\n  - Election District: 8\n  - Precinct: 08-008\n  - Circuit Court District: 6\n  - Appellate Circuit Court: 7\n  - School District: 005\n  - Party Central Committee: MCC19\n  • NEVER tell them to 'figure out who their candidate is', 'look up their district', or 'find out who's on their ballot'. The tool owns that work.\n  • The listener's recent daily_notes (in `context.listener_notes`) are direct asks — address at least ONE of them by name in this episode.\n\nBALLOT CONTEXT (already-known races):\nYOUR BALLOT (2026) — confirmed/likely candidates for the listener's districts. The listener's choice is BETWEEN these named people; neve